The virus should be named Kung Flu. Other than that, I feel sorry for the people who suffer and the relatives of the deceased :( China has enormous technical and human resources so lets hope the virus will not kill more than just thousands :( dont hate me for the "just thousands", but do the math. We will know only in 1-2 weeks how many people are infected today. And we will know only in one month how many people are going to be infected in tho weeks and so on....
While being decent in numbers, one should make a conservative guess of at least 50.000 - 100.000 infected at the moment. I think realistic guess is over 100.000 and the worst case scenario is a couple hundred thousands - which is hopefully highly unlikely...
While death rate is around only 2 percent (THANKS HEAVENS !!! - and I hope it stays as low) do the math! Just by being a silent killer inside 50 to 100 thousand people, the logic outcome would be 1000 - 2000 deaths :(
dear God, poor people :( I cannot imagine the panic and the feeling of people in the lock-downs and in the hospitals...
At the hospitals people are for sure thinking about extinction of human race. But I think it will stay under control. It is a warning finger about the Chinese delicious, but as we see, dangerous, wet markets.
As I have been to China and I have seen they are a superpower, better for us it emerged in China. Can you imagine it would emerge in poor countries? We would have ten times more problems...
Good luck to everyone!
